-- Mali Beats Ghana 3-1 in Africa Cup of Nations Third-Place Game
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-02-09T20:11:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-09/mali-beats-ghana-3-1-in-africa-cup-of-nations-third-place-game.html
Mali defeated Ghana 3-1 in the third-
place match at soccer’s Africa Cup of Nations in South Africa.  Mahamadou Samassa, Seydou Keita and Sigamary Diarra scored
for Mali at Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium in Port Elizabeth. Kwadwo
Asamoah had the goal for Ghana.  Burkina Faso plays two-time champion Nigeria in the final
tomorrow in Johannesburg. Burkina Faso is seeking its first
title in Africa’s continental championship.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  